Description

The Block class represents a block in the brick game.

The BlockSerializable class represents a serializable version of the Block object.

The Bonus class represents a bonus object in the game.

The Direction enum represents the possible directions for movement in the game.
GameEngine
The GameEngine class represents the game engine responsible for managing game updates, physics calculations, and time tracking.
GameEngine.OnAction
The interface defining actions to be performed by the game engine.

The LoadSave class is responsible for reading saved game data from a file.

This class is the main entry point for the Block Game application.

The Score class provides methods to display score-related messages in the game.
